				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yes. Well, sorta. It's still only a 2bpp plane, and that's a bigger thing in terms of visual richness than changing total content.<br /><br />The late-stage advanced mappers often provided eight independent 1KiB banks to control this, allowing for (e.g.) a quarter of tiles to be animated while half were used for fixed background things and another quarter could change as the level progressed, as well as grouped animations on random subsets of sprites.<br /><br />But between the 6502 being an 8-bit microcomputer, and memory and bandwidth on the NES being limited, there was very little pressure to go <em>past</em> 256 KiB of data.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

